        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">PureGlow Cosmetics, clean beauty mascara brand in Los Angeles. Website: minimalist design with "key ingredients" only (beeswax, vitamin E, "natural oils" - vague), no full ingredient list visible, no before/after photos, no certifications visible, one-time purchase only (no subscription), basic product shots (white background, no application photos). Monthly sales: 847 units @ $24 each = $20,328/month. Conversion rate: 1.2%. Problem: "Customers searching 'clean mascara organic' visit our site, see vague ingredients, can't verify if truly clean, leave without buying. They purchase from brands with full transparency. I'm losing sales to fear of hidden chemicals."</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-pink-50 border-[3px] border-pink-200 p-6 mb-6">
        <p class="font-black text-pink-900 text-lg mb-4">THE FIX (Week 1: Transparency + Subscription)</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Day 1-2: Built Shopify site with full ingredient list front-and-center (every ingredient listed, purpose explained, source country), added "Clean Promise" section with visible certifications (Leaping Bunny cruelty-free, USDA organic, EWG verified), uploaded real customer before/after photos (12 diverse models showing lash length, volume, no smudging), added "Subscribe & Save 20%" option (auto-delivery every 30/60/90 days), mobile-optimized product pages (ingredients readable on phone, one-tap subscribe), integrated reviews (photos of product in use, "clean ingredients verified" comments), added "Ingredient Dictionary" blog (explains each ingredient, why safe, studies backing). Cost: $2,100 (Shopify setup $1,500, photography $600). Launch: September 18, 2024.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-pink-50 border-[3px] border-pink-200 p-6 mb-6">
        <p class="font-black text-pink-900 text-lg mb-4">THE AFTER (90 Days Later)</p>
